Global Phenethyl Isobutyrate Market Insights
Phenethyl Isobutyrate Market size was valued at USD 0.25 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.45 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Phenethyl Isobutyrate Market Overview
The global Phenethyl Isobutyrate market has witnessed significant growth in recent years, with a market value of approximately USD 75 million in 2024. The demand for Phenethyl Isobutyrate is primarily driven by its applications in the fragrance, flavoring, and cosmetic industries. It is widely used in creating floral scents, enhancing food flavors, and improving cosmetic formulations. As of 2024, the global market for Phenethyl Isobutyrate is expected to continue expanding at a steady growth rate, projected to reach USD 95 million by 2027. The market growth is supported by the increasing consumer preference for natural and synthetic aroma chemicals.

